                id = "close", speaker = "Brindle Quillfeather",
                text = "*(Brindle Quillfeather stands among his beautiful useless things with the map of silences above him — eleven growing holes where grief can't reach, charted by a frivolous empathy-machine that turned out to be the only instrument in the Gate that could see the harvest at all — and whether you turned his accidental compass into an early-warning to outrun the harvest, a documented witness that can't be called mad, a guide to the heart of the unmade, a to-do list for pouring the remembering back, a whole watch of forks built by the hundred, or a measurement to damn the Court in its own chamber, you carry away the gnome's accidental wisdom: that a machine built to celebrate how much a city loved became, in a time of harvest, the one tool that could measure exactly how much it had been made to forget — and that the repair of a silence is never the machine, but the people who go to the holes and teach the world to ache again.)*",
            });

            SqSilencesThreadDialogue = g;
        }
    }
}
